
[1]absolution

   ABSOLU'TION, n. In the civil law, an acquittal or sentence of a judge
   declaring an accused person innocent. In the canon law, a remission of
   sins pronounced by a priest in favor of a penitent. Among protestants,
   a sentence by which an excommunicated person is released from his
   liability to punishment.
